Computer Automation Inc. was a computer manufacturer founded by David H Methvin in 1968, based originally in Irvine, California, United States.
In 1981 they moved the corporate offices to Boulder, Colorado, manufacturing and sales remained in Irvine. In 1985 the offices moved back to Irvine, California.  Finally in 1990 moved to Richardson, Texas, where they had opened a manufacturing and engineering development facility in 1978 as a way to escape high California tax and labor rates.
